quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,82,"So when Our Commandment came, We turned (the towns of Sodom in Palestine) upside down, and rained on them stones of baked clay, in a well-arranged manner one after another;"
  11,83,"Marked from your Lord; and they are not ever far from the Zâlimûn (polytheists, evil-doers)."
  11,84,"And to the Madyan (Midian) people (We sent) their brother Shu‘aib. He said: "
  12,43,"And the king (of Egypt) said: "
  12,44,"They said: "
  12,45,"Then the man who was released (one of the two who were in prison), now at length remembered and said: "
  13,10,"It is the same (to Him) whether any of you conceal his speech or declares it openly, whether he be hid by night or goes forth freely by day."
  13,11,"For him (each person), there are angels in succession, before and behind him.{1} They guard him by the Command of Allâh. Verily! Allâh will not change the (good) condition of a people as long as they do not change their state (of goodness) themselves (by committing sins and by being ungrateful and disobedient to Allâh). But when Allâh wills a people’s punishment, there can be no turning back of it, and they will find besides Him no protector.",footnotes:1:(V.11) See the footnote (B) of (Verse 6:61).
  13,12,"It is He Who shows you the lightning, as a fear (for travellers) and as a hope (for those who wait for rain). And it is He Who brings up (or originates) the clouds, heavy (with water)."